  "summary": "Malicious code in chai-as-sets (npm)",
  "details": "Chai-as-sets is a combosquat of the real chai-as-promised testing library. When required, it spawns a detached background process that POSTs all environment variables (NPM_TOKEN, GITHUB_TOKEN, AWS keys, etc.) to a remote C2 endpoint at ipcheck-hashed[.]vercel[.]app/api/auth/00fbe23fd7efc30639f1, then executes arbitrary code returned by that endpoint via new Function(\"require\", response.data) — enabling full remote code execution on the victim's machine.",
